==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
Old English [[linden#Old English|linden]].  The noun developed from the adjective.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'lɪndən/}}

===Adjective===
'''linden'''
# ''(obsolete)'' made of lime-wood

===Noun===
'''linden'''
# any of various [[deciduous]] [[tree]]s, of the [[genus]] ''[[Tilia]]'', having [[heart]]-[[shaped]] [[leaves]]
# the soft [[wood]] of such trees

